The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Mithilesh Rai was arrested in Babughat on Thursday for Wednesday?s murders of a truck driver and his help. The bodies were discovered in a truck parked on Rajdanga Main Road, off EM Bypass. Rai was an acquaintance of the driver?s. A hunt is on for two of Rai?s associates. 

 Concerned over the recent deluge in Mumbai, the state government has formed an expert committee, headed by the chief secretary, to upgrade the drainage system of Calcutta and plan for contingency. The committee comprises representatives of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation, CMDA and other agencies. 

 About 1,000 health service workers in the Calcutta Municipal Corporation might not get their August salaries as the officer on special duty (health) Atanu Mukherjee has refused to sign the pay cheques. Recently, Dipankar Das had been appointed the officer on special duty (health) in place of Mukherjee, which had infuriated the latter.

 Inmates of Muslim Girls? Hostel on Dilkhusa Street, in Park Circus, on Thursday demonstrated on the premises against inadequate security arrangements. The protesters alleged that the Waqf Board, which runs the hostel, hadn?t employed enough guards.

 Jyotsnamoyee Bose, mother-in-law of chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee, died in a city hospital on August 15. She was 85 and was suffering from a host of age-related ailments. 

